          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`knowledge/conventions/security.md` says `FsTrackStore` uses `reject_symlinks_below()` before the `metadata.json` atomic write, but `libs/infrastructure/src/track/fs_store.rs` never performs that check. This documents a symlink defense that the current adapter does not provide.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/security.md",
              "line": 65,
              "category": "security documentation"
            },
            {
              "message": "The new `check_approved<R, H, D>` example cannot compile as written: `ReviewCycle::get_review_states()` is only available when `R: Reviewer`, `H: ReviewHasher`, and `D: DiffGetter`, but the snippet omits those bounds. Add a `where` clause or make the example concrete.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/conventions/hexagonal-architecture.md",
              "line": 89,
              "category": "docs correctness"
